to explain our markdown, but instead of RMD, there's a QMD, uses Knitter, makes it very compatible

00:06:58.000 --> 00:07:06.239
with all the existing RMD files. One difference to highlight is that chunk options are generally

00:07:06.239 --> 00:07:12.880
encouraged to use YAML rather than put them inline. And there's just an example of

00:07:14.239 --> 00:07:20.399
a Knitter engine document, and you can see, very familiar for people who've used our markdown,

00:07:20.399 --> 00:07:25.679
you can see cross-references in here, you can see the label and caption in the code chunk.

